l relations, word order, clause linkage, and information structure. The structure of the book illustrates the fundamental importance of the analytical distinction between the onomasiological and the semasiological approach to language and language diversity. Both perspectives are integrated in most papers with a dominant focus on either the former or the latter perspective.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxSyntax. 0aTypology (Linguistics). 4aTypologie /Sprache. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aFunctional Typology.1 aAhoua, Firmin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAuwera, Johan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBakker, Dik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBohnemeyer, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCuzzolin, Pierluigi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDixon, R. M. W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHelmbrecht, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHelmbrecht, Johannes, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJendraschek, Gerd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoptjevskaja-Tamm, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKönig, Ekkehard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLuraghi, Silvia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalchukov, Andrej, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMereu, Lunella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMetzing, Dieter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id